      "side": 1,
      "message": "At your option here. What you described by e-mail makes sense, so if you’d prefer this to be a DCHECK, go for it.\n\nMy rule of thumb: a DCHECK is OK if the thing you’re trying to protect against is likely to show up in a developer’s debug build. Since your concern was refactoring accidentally moving this code under the loader lock, a DCHECK would be appropriate. A CHECK would be better if you wanted to protect against oddball field conditions not likely to be encountered (or encountered frequently) on a development system.",
